@startuml
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontColor #000000
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam ArrowColor #000000
skinparam TitleFontColor #000000

title Postgres Provider Driver Loading (After)

actor "Client/Edge Bundler" as Bundler
actor "Node.js Server Runtime" as Server
component "@xylex-group/athena\n(root entry)" as Root #E3F2FD
component "schema/postgres-provider.ts" as Provider #E8F5E9
component "loadPgPoolConstructor()\nasync lazy loader" as LazyLoader #FFFDE7
component "pg driver\n(node-postgres)" as PgDriver #FFCDD2

Bundler --> Root : import { createClient }
Root --> Provider : module can be linked safely
Provider --> LazyLoader : defines loader only
note right of Provider
No top-level runtime import from 'pg'
at module evaluation time.
end note

Server --> Provider : inspect()
Provider --> LazyLoader : await import('pg') on demand
LazyLoader --> PgDriver : load in server runtime only

note bottom of LazyLoader
pg is loaded only when introspection executes,
keeping default package imports client-safe.
end note
@enduml
